Two people died while 21 others sustained serious injuries following a road accident near Maara River bridge, Tharaka Nithi county on Sunday. The bus, belonging to Joy Kenya, was on its way to Meru from Nairobi. Maara OCPD Johnston Kabusia said the bus veered off the road into a nearby bush after its breaks failed. The injured were rushed to Chuka county referral and PCEA Chogoria mission hospitals. The bodies of the deceased were taken to to Chuka hospital mortuary. On Friday, a woman was killed and scores injured after a Kensilver Bus heading to Meru was involved in an accident at Nithi bridge. The accident occurred after the bus' brakes failed. More on this: Woman killed after bus crashes at Nithi bridge Click here for the latest political news    